text:
Niv Mizzet Parun changes:
 - Nexus of Fate (card sux)
 - High Tide (not sure why I thought this was a good idea. I play too many nonbasics and doubling my blue doesn't actually get me closer to casting NM)
 - Expansion / Explosion (card just sat in my hand a bunch. The 2nd side is way too expensive when compared to be useful and i don't need a 3rd stroke of genius / blue sun; first mode just doesn't come up a lot as useful)

 + earthquake (i always wanted more board wipes when i played. I took out some of the ones like anger of the gods, but I wanted more flexible ones-- and ones that don't hit NM)
 + subterranean tremors (same as EQ, this card is cute)
 + concentrate (i think i need more mana effective draw spells)
